==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snivel
<hw>Sniv"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Sniveled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or
<conjf>Snivelled</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sniveling</conjf> or <conjf>Snivelling</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[OE. <ets>snivelen</ets>, <ets>snevelen</ets>, <ets>snuvelen</ets>,
freg. of <ets>sneven</ets>. See <er>Sniff</er>, and cf.
<er>Snuffle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To run at the nose; to make a
snuffling noise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cry or whine with snuffling, as children; to cry
weakly or whiningly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Put stop to thy <qex>sniveling</qex> ditty.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snivel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snivel
<hw>Sniv"el</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>snofel</ets>. Cf.
<er>Snivel</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>Mucus from the nose;
snot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sniveler</ent>⟦br⟧
